## Summary

**Bug:** In the `operate` method of `BigMatrixImpl.java`, the output array was being created with the wrong size. It was using `v.length` (the length of the input vector) instead of `nRows` (the number of rows in the matrix). This caused an `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException` when the matrix had more rows than the input vector had elements.

**Fix:** Changed `new BigDecimal[v.length]` to `new BigDecimal[nRows]` so that the output vector has the correct size - equal to the number of rows in the matrix, which is the expected behavior for matrix-vector multiplication.

**Verification:** The test `org.apache.commons.math.linear.BigMatrixImplTest::testMath209` now passes, and other related tests continue to pass as well.

